  DJIA   S&P 500   GLOBAL DOW   NASDAQ   Industrial Goods      Compare to    Add          Open  146.52   Prior Close  147.12 (07/20/17)     1 Day    ITW 0.12%     DJIA -0.15%     S&P 500 -0.04%     Industrial Goods 0.36%                             Overview Profile     Overview Profile Financials Income Statement Balance Sheet Cash Flow Research & Ratings Historical Prices Options Advanced Charting              Company Info Illinois Tool Works Inc.        155 Harlem Avenue Glenview Illinois 60025 United States   Email Website Map       Employees  50,000    Sector  Industrial Machinery      Sales or Revenue  13.60 B    Industry  Industrial Goods      1Y Sales Change   1.45%     Fiscal Year Ends  December 31 Download Reports                      Description Illinois Tool Works Inc.      Illinois Tool Works, Inc. manufactures diversified range of industrial products and equipment. It operates through the following business segments: Automotive OEM, Test & Measurement and Electronics, Food Equipment, Polymers & Fluids, Welding, Construction Products, and Specialty Products. The Automotive OEM segment produces components and fasteners for automotive-related applications. The Test & Measurement and Electronics segment manufactures equipment, consumables, and related software for testing and measuring of materials, structures, gases and fluids. The Food Equipment segment supplies commercial food equipment and provides related services. The Polymers & Fluids segment provides adhesives, sealants, lubrication and cutting fluids, janitorial and hygiene products, and fluids and polymers for auto aftermarket maintenance and appearance. The Welding segment furnishes arc welding equipment, consumables and accessories for a wide array of industrial and commercial applications. The Construction Products segment makes construction fastening systems and truss products. The Specialty Products segment manufacturing beverage packaging equipment and consumables, product coding and marking equipment and consumables, and appliance components and fasteners. The company was founded by Byron L. Smith in 1912 and is headquartered in Glenview, IL.    expand             Key People Illinois Tool Works Inc.   Board of Directors    Name/Title Current Board Membership          Ernest Scott Santi, 54  Chairman & Chief Executive Officer   Illinois Tool Works, Inc.      James A. Skinner, 72  Lead Independent Director   Illinois Tool Works, Inc.      Jay L. Henderson, 60  Independent Director   Illinois Tool Works, Inc.      Richard H. Lenny, 64  Independent Director   The Museum of Science & Industry, McDonald's Corp., ConAgra Foods, Inc., Illinois Tool Works, Inc., Ravinia Festival Association, Discover Financial Services      Susan M. Crown, 57  Independent Director   The Northern Trust Co., Natural Resources Defense Council, Inc., Susan Crown Exchange, Inc., Rush University Medical Center, CARE USA, Illinois Tool Works, Inc., Navy Pier, Inc., Northern Trust Corp.      Kevin M. Warren, 53  Independent Director   Georgetown University, Community Anti-Drug Coalitions of America, Illinois Tool Works, Inc., Rochester Business Alliance      Anré D. Williams, 50  Independent Director   Illinois Tool Works, Inc.      James W. Griffith, 62  Independent Director   Illinois Tool Works, Inc., National Association of Manufacturers, University of Mount Union, Manufacturing Advocacy & Growth Network, The Magnet Group LLC, Volvo AB      Daniel J. Brutto, 59  Independent Director   United States Fund for UNICEF, United Nations Children's Fund, Innotrac Corp., Illinois Tool Works, Inc.      David H. B. Smith, 50  Independent Director   Chicago Botanic Garden, Illinois Tool Works, Inc., Northern Trust Corp., The Northern Trust Co., Carleton College      Pamela B. Strobel, 62  Independent Director   State Farm Mutual Automobile Insurance Co., Ravinia Festival Association, Illinois Tool Works, Inc., Domtar Corp., State Farm Insurance Cos.       expand    All Executives     Ernest S